### What I would do if we start coding

I would first generate:

```text
unisearch/
│
├── __init__.py
│
├── core/
│   ├── models.py
│   ├── tokenizer.py
│   └── search_result.py
│
├── providers/
│   ├── rna_provider.py
│   └── operator_provider.py
│
├── index/
│   ├── feature_index.py
│   └── token_index.py
│
├── debug/
│   ├── debug_panel.py
│   └── debug_operators.py
```

which corresponds exactly to:

```text
Stage 1
Stage 2
```

and produces the first working backend.

At that point you can search:

```text
cavity
delete
save
```

and see real Blender data instead of dummy results.

Only after that passes validation would we proceed to containers and breadcrumb discovery.

For this project, my preferred workflow is:

1. Build one stage.
2. Deliver complete code for that stage.
3. You test inside Blender.
4. We review results.
5. Move to next stage.

That minimizes risk and keeps the architecture aligned with the roadmap.
